MultiTouch Talk for Vancouver
=============================

TODO: look at
http://quirksmode.org/touchevents/

## introduction

- why touch matters
  - some stats about how many mobile devices there are
  - how many of them have touch screens
- what touch events are
  - why not just use mouse events!?
- touch events available in the spec (talk about new spec and touch events)
- browser support and stuff (show caniuse.com, quirksmode.org table)

## development tips

- tip: don't render too often
  - http://smus.com/x/touch/tracker.html vs tracker-slow.html
- tip: set viewport
- tip: disable scrolling on iOS
- tip: click delays on mobile devices
(http://code.google.com/mobile/articles/fast_buttons.html)
- tip: orientation probably matters.
- tip: -webkit-touch-callout: none;

## cool demos (show on ipad)

single touch:
- http://quirksmode.org/m/tests/drag.html basic touch
- everytimezone.com for nice touch interface

multitouch:
- tracking fingers on the surface
    http://smus.com/x/touch/controller/Touches.html
- multitouch drag
    http://quirksmode.org/m/tests/drag.html basic touch

